    "help": {
      "topics": [
        {
          "id": "overview",
          "title": "Tech Modern",
          "content": "# Tech Modern\n\nColor themes inspired by iconic technology companies.\n\n## Themes\n\n### Redmond (Dark)\nWindows 11 dark mode with Mica-style surfaces. Cool cyan-blue accents and soft pastel highlights on smooth, layered darks. Uses Segoe UI and Cascadia Code fonts.\n\n### Mountain View (Light)\nGoogle's Material You in full color. Bold red, green, yellow, and blue primaries pop against a tinted blue surface — playful and unmistakably Google. Features a Google Blue accent gradient.\n\n### Cupertino (Light)\nApple's refined minimalism. Pure whites, careful grays, and restrained system accent colors from the Human Interface Guidelines. Uses Apple system fonts including SF Mono.\n\n### AI Lab (Light)\nWarm cream backgrounds with burnt-sienna orange accents, inspired by the thoughtful, human-centered aesthetic of modern AI research labs.\n\n### Seattle (Dark)\nBold orange on dark navy — an e-commerce giant's signature palette reimagined for code, with cloud-blue accents. Features a navy background gradient and an orange accent gradient.\n\n## Usage\n\nInstall the plugin and select any Tech Modern theme from **Settings > Appearance > Theme**."
        }
      ]
